result.execSummary:
The defendant Dangnecko Tirrice Dickerson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dangnecko Tirrice Dickerson in court with attorney Gabriela A Leija.  Margaret Anne Kunisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by parties.  Additional statements by :  John A. 
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction.  COURT IMPOSED BUT STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 months with the following conditions:
- Anger management program. 
- 40 hours of community service. 
- Mental health evaluation. 
- No contact with John A. 
- Pay restitution in the amount of $75.00 to John A. during term of probation or civil judgment. 
- Pay all costs and surcharges during term of probation or civil judgment.

Case recalled.    Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.   Court vacates jury trial date of 11-30-2015.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 45.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 6, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
